VL  - 47
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents an editorial that discusses the value of editors of periodicals. The author details staff changes that are taking place in the editorial offices of the Academy of Management Journal and states that he believes editors do not matter sometimes, especially from the vantage-point of an external observer. The author states that there is little variation in how editors make decisions or chose reviewers, but also states that editors are important as educators to their peers.
AB  - The article presents an editorial that discusses the value of editors of periodicals. The author details staff changes that are taking place in the editorial offices of the Academy of Management Journal and states that he believes editors do not matter sometimes, especially from the vantage-point of an external observer. The author states that there is little variation in how editors make decisions or chose reviewers, but also states that editors are important as educators to their peers.
